						<div class="postbody">That's great to know dvdmth. I was wondering if my project was duplicating something that already existed, but with what you wrote I can see that's definitely not the case. My device will work with all games because it is invisible to the rest of the system. 
<br />
<br />Hijacking the NMI routine has some serious drawbacks. You can't control variables that are changed inside the NMI. When you consider that most of the game code is inside the NMI routine, it's very limiting. I don't see the PAR being much more useful than a game genie.</div>

